  "why_is_this_an_issue": "Direct type comparisons are less flexible, since they only support exact type matching. `isinstance()` allows for more flexibility by checking if an object is an instance of a class or one of its subclasses.",
  "how_to_fix": "Replace direct type comparisons with `isinstance()`",
